By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Erstwhile President of the Senate, Dr. Abubakar Bukola Saraki, has congratulated Dr. Samson Olasupo Ayokunle on his re-election as the President of the Christian Association of Nigeria (CAN). In a statement issued by his Media Office, Saraki also congratulated Christians across the nation on the re-emergence of Dr. Ayokunle, whom he described as a man of immense faith. “I congratulate the Christian Association of Nigeria (CAN) and all Nigerians of the Christian faith on the re-election of Dr. Samson Ayokunle as the President of CAN. “Dr. Ayokunle, a man of immense faith, has over the years demonstrated his commitment to strengthening the unity, peace and development of Nigeria through his work in the church. “As he begins a second tenure, I wish him and all Christians across Nigeria immense success as we work to forge a stronger nation for all under the Almighty,” Saraki stated. 